===Deep fried dishes===
[[Image:Zhaliang.jpg|thumb|right|[[Zhaliang|Zaa Leung]], a common dish in a Cantonese breakfast.]]

There are a small number of deep-fried dishes in Cantonese cuisine, which can often be found as [[street food]]. They have been extensively documented in [[History of Colonial Hong Kong (1800s–1930s)|colonial Hong Kong]] records of the 19th and 20th centuries. A few are synonymous with Cantonese breakfast and lunch,<ref name="Wordie">{{cite book |title= Streets: Exploring Hong Kong Island|last= Wordie|first= Jason|authorlink= |coauthors= |year= 2002|publisher= [[Hong Kong University Press]]|location= Hong Kong|isbn= 962-209-563-1|page= |pages= |url= |accessdate=}}</ref> even though these are also part of other cuisines.

