=== Slow-cooked soup ===
[[Image:WintermelonSoup.jpg|thumb|right|Winter melon soup]]

Slow-cooked soup, or ''lou fo tong'' ({{zh|s=老火汤|t=老火湯|p=lǎohuǒ tāng|j=lou5 fo2 tong1}}) in the Cantonese dialect (literally meaning ''old fire-cooked soup'') is usually a clear [[broth]] prepared by simmering meat and other ingredients over a low heat for several hours. Chinese herbs are often used as ingredients.

Soup chain stores or delivery outlets in Cantonese-dominated cities such as Hong Kong serve this dish due to the long preparation time of slow-cooked soup.

