===Little Pot rice===
[[Image:Littlebowlrice.jpg|thumb|right|Little pan rice]]

Little Pot rice ({{zh|s=煲仔饭|t=煲仔飯|p=bāozǎifàn|j=bou1 zai2 faan6}}) are dishes cooked and served in a flat-bottomed pot (as opposed to a round-bottomed [[wok]]). Usually this is a [[saucepan]] or [[braising]] pan (see [[clay pot cooking]]). Such dishes are cooked by covering and steaming, making the rice and ingredients very hot and soft. Usually the ingredients are layered on top of the rice with little or no mixing in between. Many standard combinations exist.

